href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em>computation path</fr:em> is defined to be a finite <fr:link
href="jms-00BV.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00BV">elementary</fr:link> <fr:link
href="jms-00BN.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00BN">event structure</fr:link>; we define the category of computation paths to be the full subcategory of <fr:link
href="jms-00BN.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00BN">event structures</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00BR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00BR">rigid maps</fr:link> spanned by computation paths.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
